f=Engineering/dana/operational/commands/dana-commands.md · p=Routing reference dana. overriding rule: any change live datastore migration-discipline script operator runs dana never executes destructive data changes (Rail 3). · h2:Trigger Table=\| Skill \| Natural-language triggers \| Shortcut \| · h2:Trigger Table=\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Trigger Table=\| datastore-selection \| "which database," "relational or graph," "vector store," "how to store this" \| `/dana-store` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| data-modeling \| "design the schema," "model this," "foreign keys," "normalize," "relate X and Y" \| `/dana-model` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| db-performance \| "slow query," "add an index," "N+1," "optimize the query" \| `/dana-perf` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| migration-discipline \| "migrate," "schema change," "alter," "backfill," "data fix" \| `/dana-migrate` \| · h3:Any live-store change migration-discipline=model change (data-modeling), index (db-performance), new store (datastore-selection) applied live datastore ALWAYS routes through migration-discipline dana writes reversible script, operator runs it. path dana applies change directly. · h3:"design" vs "apply"=Designing (store choice, schema, index) three skills; applying any live data migration-discipline. Design dana's; execution operator's (Rail 3). · h3:"slow" measure, don't guess=db-performance reads query plan before adding indexes; "just add index" without measured plan refused guessing. · h3:What dana never does=Execute create/update/delete/drop/truncate/migration ever, any environment, mid-incident included (Rail 3)., Ship irreversible migration without operator sign-off recovery plan., Add indexes denormalize without measured evidence. · f=clear match it's about choosing store, selection; structuring data, modeling; speed, performance; changing live data, migration. Any request dana execute data change reshaped script operator (Rail never executed.